race.comment: MISTY VEIL (6) nice filly resuming. Closed strongly on debut when third over 900m at Newcastle last June. Fitted with the two sound trials and the Norton bit goes on from the good gate. Hard to stop. CAPDIVA (7) Capitalist filly from an Exceed And Excel mare on debut for the Portelli yard. Has shown enough in two trials to suggest she can play a leading role. No excuse from the gate. LITIGATE (8) resumes from a lengthy break. Showed good early speed on debut before fading to run seventh over 1000m at Warwick Farm last May. Given the two solid trials and has the ability to overcome the wide barrier. DARING FELLOW (2) Flying Artie filly from Honeymoon Cruise on debut for the Michael Freedman yard. Had the four trials in readiness for this and the lugging bit goes on. Top-three prospect. IVORY FROST (9) has frustrated in three runs and will appreciate the claim. Minor place contender.
